I knew that the God of justice would set all matters right in his own time and in his own way.

00:37:49.829 --> 00:37:54.829
Jehovah answered my prayer in such a wonderful way.

00:37:54.829 --> 00:38:00.829
I never forgot where this incredible blessing had come from.

00:38:00.829 --> 00:38:08.190
There is no rock like our God.

00:38:08.190 --> 00:38:12.190
Did you see the grief on Hannah's face in that first picture?

00:38:12.190 --> 00:38:16.190
The next piece of art, she's peaceful in tranquil.

00:38:16.190 --> 00:38:20.190
And she's voicing her faith in Jehovah her rock.

00:38:20.190 --> 00:38:26.190
From despair to calmness of heart, how did that happen?

00:38:26.190 --> 00:38:29.190
Versus 10 and 11.

00:38:29.190 --> 00:38:33.190
She demonstrated faith in several ways.

00:38:33.190 --> 00:38:40.190
And we can do the same as we face our own boom, boom, one, two punch of trials and frustrations of life.

00:38:41.190 --> 00:38:43.190
Verse 10.

00:38:43.190 --> 00:38:52.190
Hannah was extremely bitter and she began to pray to Jehovah and to weep uncontrollably.

00:38:52.190 --> 00:38:57.190
She was extremely bitter, but she prayed.

00:38:57.190 --> 00:39:02.190
She cried uncontrollably, but she prayed to Jehovah.

00:39:02.190 --> 00:39:09.190
In your agonizing circumstances, no matter how agitated, find a quiet place.

00:39:09.190 --> 00:39:15.190
If only in your mind and pour out your heart to Jehovah.

00:39:15.190 --> 00:39:19.190
Well, how else did Hannah show her faith?

00:39:19.190 --> 00:39:24.190
Well, in that very prayer, she did ask Jehovah for a blessing,

00:39:24.190 --> 00:39:28.190
but she also promised to give him something in return.

00:39:28.190 --> 00:39:29.190
Verse 11.

00:39:29.190 --> 00:39:34.050
And she made this vow.

00:39:34.050 --> 00:39:41.050
O Jehovah of armies, if you look upon the affliction of your servant and remember me,

00:39:41.050 --> 00:39:47.050
and you do not forget your servant, and give to your servant a male child,

00:39:47.050 --> 00:39:53.050
I will give him to Jehovah all the days of his life, and no razor will touch his head.

00:39:53.050 --> 00:40:02.050
Yes, she was going to give her son as a Nazareth from birth to serve Jehovah all his days,

00:40:02.050 --> 00:40:07.050
a sterling example of faith.

00:40:07.050 --> 00:40:11.050
Well, what else likely strengthened Hannah's faith?

00:40:11.050 --> 00:40:17.050
Examples of faithful women who came before her, with similar circumstances.

00:40:17.050 --> 00:40:22.050
Do you remember Rachel and her sister, Leah?

00:40:22.050 --> 00:40:28.050
They were both married to Jacob, and like Hannah, Rachel had no children.

00:40:28.050 --> 00:40:31.050
And there were issues between the two because of this.

00:40:31.050 --> 00:40:39.050
But you see, Hannah could look back on that example and see how Jehovah helped faithful Rachel to prosper.

00:40:39.050 --> 00:40:42.050
It bolstered her faith.

00:40:42.050 --> 00:40:46.050
Well, what's another way that Hannah showed faith?

00:40:46.050 --> 00:40:52.050
Well, despite being distraught, so distraught that she would weep and could not eat,

00:40:52.050 --> 00:40:55.050
she continued her spiritual routine.

00:40:55.050 --> 00:41:02.050
Verse 7 says that she would go the tabernacle faithfully year after year.

00:41:02.050 --> 00:41:10.050
13 through 16, she was misjudged by the high priest, but she continued her spiritual routine.

00:41:10.050 --> 00:41:18.050
Now, as we said at the outset, the punches that life throws us are different from Hannah's,

00:41:18.050 --> 00:41:23.050
but we too can have the same strong faith that she did.

00:41:23.050 --> 00:41:28.050
Now, in the following dramatization, though the trial is different,

00:41:28.050 --> 00:41:32.050
note how the sister shows faith like that of Hannah.

00:41:32.050 --> 00:41:43.860
I could tell from the doctor's voice the news wasn't good.

00:41:43.860 --> 00:42:06.230
I just didn't expect my health to worsen so quickly.

00:42:06.230 --> 00:42:40.670
I tried to act like everything was fine, but I was fine.

00:42:40.670 --> 00:42:48.460
I wasn't.

00:42:48.460 --> 00:43:10.110
Going to Jehovah, knowing he would listen and understand that's what got me through.

00:43:10.110 --> 00:43:18.099
No one really knew what I was going through.

00:43:18.099 --> 00:43:22.219
Not even my friends.

00:43:22.219 --> 00:43:46.190
I felt like Hannah totally misunderstood.

00:43:46.190 --> 00:43:50.190
But she had faith that Jehovah would set matters straight.

00:43:50.190 --> 00:43:56.860
And he did.

00:43:56.860 --> 00:44:03.750
For Hannah and for me, but more than that,

00:44:03.750 --> 00:44:07.750
he reminded me that I wouldn't have to deal with this illness alone.

00:44:07.750 --> 00:44:16.030
The sister's circumstances were different,

00:44:16.030 --> 00:44:21.030
but she drew strength from Hannah's strong faith in Jehovah.

00:44:21.030 --> 00:44:24.030
No matter what the circumstances are,

00:44:24.030 --> 00:44:28.030
how can we imitate the example of that faith?

00:44:28.030 --> 00:44:31.030
Well, there's many different ways, but let's review a few.

00:44:31.030 --> 00:44:37.030
First Peter 5.9, Satan tries to beat us up and knock us down,

00:44:37.030 --> 00:44:39.030
but we're not alone.

00:44:39.030 --> 00:44:42.030
There are others who experience the same trials.

00:44:42.030 --> 00:44:44.030
First Peter 5.9,

00:44:44.030 --> 00:44:52.590
but take your stand against him, firm in the faith,

00:44:52.590 --> 00:44:56.590
knowing that the same kind of sufferings are being experienced

00:44:56.590 --> 00:45:00.590
by the entire association of your brothers in the world.

00:45:00.590 --> 00:45:03.590
Reflect on Jehovah's dealings with other faithful ones,

00:45:03.590 --> 00:45:08.030
both in the past and in the present day.

00:45:08.030 --> 00:45:14.030
Now in 1 Samuel 112, it says that Hannah prayed for a long time

00:45:14.030 --> 00:45:16.030
before Jehovah.

00:45:16.030 --> 00:45:20.030
We too can gain relief through fervent, persistent,

00:45:20.030 --> 00:45:23.030
and specific prayers.

00:45:23.030 --> 00:45:26.030
Colossians 4 says persevere in prayer.

00:45:26.030 --> 00:45:29.030
When we pray to Jehovah,

00:45:29.030 --> 00:45:34.030
leave it with him, confident that he will help.

00:45:34.030 --> 00:45:37.030
And recall that Hannah was extremely bitter.

00:45:37.030 --> 00:45:39.030
She was crying uncontrollably.

00:45:39.030 --> 00:45:43.030
But after she poured her feelings out to Jehovah,

00:45:43.030 --> 00:45:45.030
verse 18 says,

00:45:45.030 --> 00:45:47.030
she went on her way and ate,

00:45:47.030 --> 00:45:51.030
and her face was no longer downcast.

00:45:51.030 --> 00:45:54.030
And then after Jehovah acted in her behalf,

00:45:54.030 --> 00:45:56.030
Hannah remembered that,

00:45:56.030 --> 00:45:58.030
and she went back to Jehovah in prayer

00:45:58.030 --> 00:46:04.030
and prayed the beautiful prayer in 1 Samuel 2.

00:46:04.030 --> 00:46:06.030
Finally, like Hannah,

00:46:06.030 --> 00:46:08.030
even if discouraged,

00:46:08.030 --> 00:46:12.030
we need to maintain a good spiritual routine.

00:46:12.030 --> 00:46:17.030
If we allow distress to paralyze us,

00:46:17.030 --> 00:46:22.030
in effect, we become a stationary punching bag for Satan.

00:46:22.030 --> 00:46:24.030
Stay nimble on your feet spiritually,

00:46:24.030 --> 00:46:28.030
active in your theocratic routine.

00:46:28.030 --> 00:46:30.030
And like Paul, aim your blows.

00:46:30.030 --> 00:46:32.030
Do not strike the air.

00:46:32.030 --> 00:46:36.030
Fight back against Satan and his tactics.

00:46:36.030 --> 00:46:38.030
If we do all these things,

00:46:38.030 --> 00:46:43.030
our bond with Jehovah will grow ever stronger.

00:46:43.030 --> 00:46:45.030
And,

00:46:45.030 --> 00:46:51.030
Jehovah will reward our faith like he did for Hannah.

00:46:51.030 --> 00:46:53.030
And now, Brother Harold Corcoran,

00:46:53.030 --> 00:46:55.030
a helper for the publishing committee,

00:46:55.030 --> 00:46:58.030
will present the next talk of this symposium,

00:46:58.030 --> 00:47:01.030
imitate women of strong faith,

00:47:01.030 --> 00:47:03.030
the captive Israelite girl.

00:47:03.030 --> 00:47:12.710
In the 11th century BCE,

00:47:12.710 --> 00:47:16.710
the nation of Syria would often attack Israel,

00:47:16.710 --> 00:47:19.710
capturing many and making many of their slaves,

00:47:19.710 --> 00:47:21.710
even children.

00:47:21.710 --> 00:47:24.710
Notice how the Bible describes one of these raids

00:47:24.710 --> 00:47:27.710
at 2 Kings chapter 5.

00:47:27.710 --> 00:47:29.710
2 Kings chapter 5,

00:47:29.710 --> 00:47:31.710
and in verse 1,

00:47:31.710 --> 00:47:35.710
we are told that Naomi was the army chief of the Syrians.

00:47:35.710 --> 00:47:37.710
He was a mighty warrior,

00:47:37.710 --> 00:47:40.710
but he was also very sick with leprosy.

00:47:40.710 --> 00:47:42.710
But notice verse 2.

00:47:42.710 --> 00:47:44.710
On wonder of their raids,

00:47:44.710 --> 00:47:47.710
the Syrians had taken captive from the land of Israel,

00:47:47.710 --> 00:47:48.710
a little girl,

00:47:48.710 --> 00:47:51.710
who became a servant to Naaman's wife.

00:47:51.710 --> 00:47:54.710
Can you picture this little girl being ripped away

00:47:54.710 --> 00:47:55.710
from her parents?

00:47:55.710 --> 00:47:57.710
It was frightening for her.

00:47:57.710 --> 00:47:59.710
She was taken to a strange land

00:47:59.710 --> 00:48:01.710
with people that were intimidating,

00:48:01.710 --> 00:48:04.710
and they worshipped many false gods.

00:48:05.710 --> 00:48:08.710
In that very difficult circumstance,

00:48:08.710 --> 00:48:11.710
how was this little girl required

00:48:11.710 --> 00:48:14.710
to exercise strong faith?

00:48:14.710 --> 00:48:16.710
Please note the answer to this question

00:48:16.710 --> 00:48:21.820
and the following video.

00:48:21.820 --> 00:48:25.820
I remember the day the soldiers took me away.

00:48:25.820 --> 00:48:28.820
I had never felt more alone.

00:48:28.820 --> 00:48:31.820
My home, my friends,

00:48:31.820 --> 00:48:34.820
everything I knew was gone.

00:48:35.820 --> 00:48:37.820
But I still had Jehovah.

00:48:37.820 --> 00:48:43.829
The master of the house was very sick.

00:48:43.829 --> 00:48:46.829
He was in pain.

00:48:46.829 --> 00:48:48.829
Elijah could help him.

00:48:48.829 --> 00:48:51.829
I had heard about Elijah's miracles.

00:48:51.829 --> 00:48:54.829
He had even raised the dead.

00:48:54.829 --> 00:48:57.829
I knew Elijah could cure him,

00:48:57.829 --> 00:49:01.829
and Jehovah gave me the courage to speak up.

00:49:01.829 --> 00:49:08.539
Despite being away from her parents,

00:49:08.539 --> 00:49:12.539
this little girl exercised strong faith.

00:49:12.539 --> 00:49:14.539
Where did she get that faith?

00:49:14.539 --> 00:49:16.539
Well, no doubt her parents had inculcated

00:49:16.539 --> 00:49:19.539
love and trust for Jehovah in her.

00:49:19.539 --> 00:49:22.539
But she also had things that were happening

00:49:22.539 --> 00:49:25.539
in her lifetime that would build her faith.

00:49:25.539 --> 00:49:27.539
For example, she would have known

00:49:27.539 --> 00:49:31.539
about the miracles of the prophet Elijah.

00:49:31.539 --> 00:49:33.539
And how was Jehovah's Spirit?

00:49:33.539 --> 00:49:35.539
He performed many miracles,

00:49:35.539 --> 00:49:39.539
including raising a little boy from the dead.

00:49:39.539 --> 00:49:41.539
This little girl could have reason.

00:49:41.539 --> 00:49:45.539
Why if Jehovah can raise a little boy from death?

00:49:45.539 --> 00:49:50.539
He can certainly cure my master from his disease.

00:49:50.539 --> 00:49:53.539
Well, what did she do with this faith and trust?

00:49:53.539 --> 00:49:55.539
She spoke up courageously.

00:49:55.539 --> 00:49:57.539
Notice her words to her mistress

00:49:57.539 --> 00:50:02.539
as recorded at Second Kings chapter 5 and verse 3.

00:50:02.539 --> 00:50:04.539
She said to her mistress,

00:50:04.539 --> 00:50:08.539
if only my Lord would visit the prophet in Samaria,

00:50:08.539 --> 00:50:12.539
then He would cure him of his laprosy.

00:50:12.539 --> 00:50:14.539
Such bonus.

00:50:14.539 --> 00:50:16.539
And because she spoke up,

00:50:16.539 --> 00:50:19.539
Naman went to Israel,

00:50:19.539 --> 00:50:23.539
God in touch with Elijah the prophet,

00:50:23.539 --> 00:50:24.539
humbled himself,

00:50:24.539 --> 00:50:26.539
listened to the instructions,

00:50:26.539 --> 00:50:30.539
and was completely cured of the laprosy.

00:50:30.539 --> 00:50:33.539
But something else very important occurred.

00:50:33.539 --> 00:50:36.539
Because of Naman coming to know about Jehovah,

00:50:36.539 --> 00:50:38.539
what did he declare?

00:50:38.539 --> 00:50:40.539
At Second Kings 5, 15, he said,

00:50:40.539 --> 00:50:44.539
Now I know there is no God anywhere in the earth,

00:50:44.539 --> 00:50:46.539
but in Israel.

00:50:46.539 --> 00:50:50.539
And Naman also vowed that he would never serve any other gods,

00:50:50.539 --> 00:50:53.539
but Jehovah.

00:50:53.539 --> 00:50:57.539
How happy Naman and his entire household was when he went home.

00:50:57.539 --> 00:50:59.539
Not only was he cured of his laprosy,

00:50:59.539 --> 00:51:05.539
but now he was a happy, joyful servant of Jehovah.

00:51:05.539 --> 00:51:07.539
Well, it's not just in Bible times

00:51:07.539 --> 00:51:10.539
that good experiences like this have occurred.

00:51:10.539 --> 00:51:13.539
As you watch the following dramatization,

00:51:13.539 --> 00:51:15.539
notice how one of our sisters

00:51:15.539 --> 00:51:17.539
shows strong faith

00:51:17.539 --> 00:51:20.539
even under the most difficult of circumstances.

00:51:20.539 --> 00:51:27.150
I was taken from my home,

00:51:27.150 --> 00:51:32.460
my husband,

00:51:32.460 --> 00:51:34.460
and my spiritual family.

00:51:34.460 --> 00:51:39.730
I was imprisoned for my faith.

00:51:39.730 --> 00:51:50.760
It was another world.

00:51:50.760 --> 00:51:52.760
It wasn't easy staying strong.

00:51:52.760 --> 00:52:05.170
Every time I asked for a Bible,

00:52:05.170 --> 00:52:07.170
the answer was no.

00:52:07.170 --> 00:52:19.500
But God's word was already in my heart.

00:52:19.500 --> 00:52:24.059
So I did what I loved the most.

00:52:24.059 --> 00:52:26.059
I talked about God's kingdom.

00:52:26.059 --> 00:52:32.949
Many of those I preached to seemed cold at first.

00:52:32.949 --> 00:52:35.949
But genuine love and the warmth of God's word

00:52:35.949 --> 00:52:40.489
just seemed to melt their hearts.

00:52:40.489 --> 00:52:45.489
Sometimes speaking up took more courage than I thought I had.

00:52:45.489 --> 00:52:49.489
But not more courage than Jehovah could give me.

00:52:49.489 --> 00:53:08.400
It was hard to look beyond the locks and uniforms.

00:53:08.400 --> 00:53:13.400
But God's will is that all sorts of people learn about him.

00:53:13.400 --> 00:53:17.400
So I spoke about my God, Jehovah.

00:53:17.400 --> 00:53:53.719
I knew that even behind prison bars,

00:53:53.719 --> 00:54:06.070
Jehovah would give me the strength to help others.

00:54:06.070 --> 00:54:10.070
At this point, we'd like to address our young ones in the audience.

00:54:10.070 --> 00:54:13.070
You too can have strong faith

00:54:13.070 --> 00:54:15.070
like the little Israelite girl

00:54:15.070 --> 00:54:18.070
and tell others about Jehovah.

00:54:18.070 --> 00:54:22.070
Remember the words of Romans chapter 10 verses 13 and 14?

00:54:22.070 --> 00:54:26.070
It is so important that people know about Jehovah.

00:54:26.070 --> 00:54:29.070
But how can they know about him and gain salvation

00:54:29.070 --> 00:54:32.070
