Like Martha, we can build our faith in the resurrection

01:25:41.380 --> 01:25:46.380
by carefully considering all that God's Word says about it.

01:25:46.380 --> 01:25:53.380
Think of all the evidence there is that Jesus was resurrected.

01:25:53.380 --> 01:25:58.380
The scriptures show clearly that after His death and resurrection,

01:25:58.380 --> 01:26:03.380
Jesus showed Himself alive to His disciples.

01:26:03.380 --> 01:26:08.380
He also appeared to Saul of Tarsus who became the Apostle Paul.

01:26:08.380 --> 01:26:11.380
In His letter to the Corinthians,

01:26:11.380 --> 01:26:17.380
Paul points out that more than 500 brothers saw the resurrected Jesus.

01:26:17.380 --> 01:26:21.380
And to show that it was not just hearsay,

01:26:21.380 --> 01:26:26.380
Paul tells us that most of those eyewitnesses were still alive

01:26:26.380 --> 01:26:29.380
when he wrote to the Corinthians.

01:26:29.380 --> 01:26:39.380
Yes, they were living witnesses who could verify the fact that Jesus was resurrected from the dead.

01:26:39.380 --> 01:26:47.380
And think about the inspired assurance that we have at Revelation 21, 3 and 4,

01:26:47.380 --> 01:26:53.380
that the time is coming when death will be no more.

01:26:53.380 --> 01:27:02.380
When you think about it, who is it that declares that death will be no more at Revelation 21, 3 and 4?

01:27:02.380 --> 01:27:07.380
None other than the resurrected Jesus Christ.

01:27:07.380 --> 01:27:15.380
We do well to imitate Martha by maintaining strong faith when we face the loss of a loved one.

01:27:15.380 --> 01:27:19.380
No, it's not easy. It's painful.

01:27:19.380 --> 01:27:27.380
But we can do it knowing full well that this life is not all there is.

01:27:27.380 --> 01:27:33.380
All true Christians must have faith in the resurrection.

01:27:33.380 --> 01:27:42.380
Faith that the dead will live again and that death will be done away with in God's new world.

01:27:43.380 --> 01:27:50.380
Jehovah and his son rewarded the faith of Martha, Mary and Lazarus.

01:27:50.380 --> 01:27:57.380
We will be rewarded too if we build strong faith like that of Martha.

01:27:57.380 --> 01:28:06.630
Brother Garrett Lush, a member of the governing body will now present the final talk of this symposium.

01:28:07.630 --> 01:28:13.630
Imitate women of strong faith, modern-day examples.

01:28:13.630 --> 01:28:27.220
Over the years, there were many sisters without standing faith.

01:28:27.220 --> 01:28:31.220
Sister Matsui Ishi was one of them.

01:28:31.220 --> 01:28:35.220
She was born in Japan in 1909.

01:28:35.220 --> 01:28:41.220
Although she grew up in the Buddhist family, she had a thirst for Bible knowledge.

01:28:41.220 --> 01:28:49.220
In 1918, the Spanish flu hit her area and she saw lots of coffins with dead bodies.

01:28:49.220 --> 01:28:57.220
She and her elders sister both also caught the Spanish flu and the week later her sister died.

01:28:57.220 --> 01:29:04.220
She wondered, why do people die and what happens to them at death?

01:29:04.220 --> 01:29:15.220
In 1928, when Matsui was 19, her father arranged for her to marry Jesus Ishi a jealous Buddhist.

01:29:15.220 --> 01:29:22.220
Matsui was introduced to the truth in Osaka through the book The Heart of God.

01:29:22.220 --> 01:29:31.220
That was given to her by a brother who lived in a neighboring house that belonged to the International Bible Students Association.

01:29:31.220 --> 01:29:40.220
Matsui was baptized in March 1929 and her husband, Giso, was baptized a short time later.

01:29:40.220 --> 01:29:50.220
In June 1939, when she was 30 years old, she and her husband were arrested and were separated from each other.

01:29:50.220 --> 01:29:54.220
This certainly called for faith.

01:29:54.220 --> 01:30:01.220
She said that she nearly died when she was in solitary confinement for almost a year.

01:30:01.220 --> 01:30:11.220
Matsui was released toward the end of 1944 and she was reunited with Giso after World War II ended.

01:30:11.220 --> 01:30:18.039
Both she and her husband had remained faithful.

01:30:18.039 --> 01:30:22.039
Let us now consider another encouraging example.

01:30:22.039 --> 01:30:29.039
Right after World War II ended, far away from Japan in Estonia, Northeastern Europe,

01:30:29.039 --> 01:30:40.039
Ella Tom was introduced to the truth in April 1945 and was baptized in August 1946 at age 20.

01:30:40.039 --> 01:30:49.039
She was arrested by the Communists on December 27, 1950 and sentenced to imprisonment.

01:30:49.039 --> 01:30:57.039
She was sent to a slave labor camp in Russia, the infamous Wakuta camp, above the Arctic Circle,

01:30:57.039 --> 01:31:05.039
and later to other prison camps, 250 miles of 400 kilometers southeast of Moscow.

01:31:05.039 --> 01:31:09.039
The sisters continued to be spiritually minded.

01:31:09.039 --> 01:31:17.039
They made miniature copies of watchtower and put them inside bars of soap and resealed the soap.

01:31:17.039 --> 01:31:20.039
This certainly called for faith.

01:31:20.039 --> 01:31:30.039
She did not have to serve for 13 years but actually was released on May 4, 1956, after five and a half years.

01:31:30.039 --> 01:31:34.039
The year after, she married Brother Lempid Tom.

01:31:34.039 --> 01:31:45.699
However, the threat of searches and arrests continued until the preaching work was legalized in Estonia in 1991.

01:31:45.699 --> 01:32:06.020
In the following video, note some other details regarding the lives of these two faithful women, Matsui Ishi and Ella Tom.

01:32:06.020 --> 01:32:16.020
For nearly a year, I had been held in solitary confinement in a tiny filthy, bug-infested prison cell.

01:32:16.020 --> 01:32:28.560
Five and a half years after my arrest, I was released.

01:32:28.560 --> 01:32:36.560
If we truly rely on Jehovah, really love him and cry out in a heart for his help,

01:32:36.560 --> 01:32:56.260
just as he did not forsake me, he will not forsake his servants.

01:32:56.260 --> 01:33:00.260
They arrested me and took me in for questioning.

01:33:00.260 --> 01:33:08.149
An interrogator invited me to sign a document stating that I would discontinue preaching.

01:33:08.149 --> 01:33:18.779
I said, I would rather live in prison with my relationship with God intact than be free and lose his approval.

01:33:18.779 --> 01:33:23.779
My determination has been to heed the Bible admonition.

01:33:23.779 --> 01:33:27.779
Trust in Jehovah and do good.

01:33:27.779 --> 01:33:40.500
I have learned that doing this leads to receiving the requests of your heart.

01:33:40.500 --> 01:33:46.500
How did the sisters Ishi and Tom show faith?

01:33:46.500 --> 01:33:50.500
This turned with me to Psalm 37.

01:33:50.500 --> 01:34:00.500
Sister Ishi had faith that Jehovah would not abandon her in line with Psalm 37, 25, which reads,

01:34:01.500 --> 01:34:12.159
I was once young and now I'm old, but I have not seen anyone righteous abandoned nor his children looking for bread.

01:34:12.159 --> 01:34:18.159
Her faith had her to endure difficult tests of integrity.

01:34:18.159 --> 01:34:31.159
She was arrested on June 21, 1939 and taken to a police station and put into a dark cell with suit hanging from the ceiling.

01:34:31.159 --> 01:34:38.159
The after she was transferred to another location and put into solitary confinement.

01:34:38.159 --> 01:34:46.159
Her husband was also arrested and she did not see him until the war had ended.

01:34:46.159 --> 01:34:54.159
I nearly died in that cell, she said, but she was exposed to another test too.

01:34:54.159 --> 01:35:06.159
When interrogated, she found out from the officials that Junso Akashi, the overseer of the Japan branch, had abandoned the truth.

01:35:06.159 --> 01:35:12.159
Sister Ishi replied, Akashi is only an imperfect human.

01:35:12.159 --> 01:35:20.500
He is no longer my brother. Sister Ishi remained loyal.

01:35:20.500 --> 01:35:27.500
Similarly, Sister Tom from Estonia refused to compromise or to abandon her faith.

01:35:27.500 --> 01:35:44.680
She prayed and meditated on Bible principles in order to endure like Psalm 119 verses 97 and 98 say,

01:35:44.680 --> 01:35:50.680
How I do love your law, I ponder over it all day long.

01:35:50.680 --> 01:36:00.659
Your commandment makes me wiser than my enemies because it is with me forever.

01:36:00.659 --> 01:36:09.659
In 1949, Ella Tom was arrested by the communists. They took her in for questioning.

01:36:09.659 --> 01:36:19.659
She reports, forced to remove all my clothing and being watched by young police officers, I felt humiliated.

01:36:19.659 --> 01:36:28.199
Yet after I prayed to Jehovah, peace and calmness of heart came over me.

01:36:28.199 --> 01:36:33.199
Next I was put in a tiny cell where I could not even lie down.

01:36:33.199 --> 01:36:38.199
I was taken out only for interrogations.

01:36:38.199 --> 01:36:43.199
Officers would say, we are not asking you to deny the existence of God.

01:36:43.199 --> 01:36:49.199
Just stop your stupid preaching. You can have a promising future.

01:36:49.199 --> 01:37:00.930
And they would threaten, quote, Do you want to live or do you want to die with your God on the fields of Siberia?

01:37:00.930 --> 01:37:08.930
She said, For three days I was prevented from falling asleep between the repeated interrogations.

01:37:08.930 --> 01:37:13.930
Meditation on Bible principles helped me to endure.

01:37:13.930 --> 01:37:23.930
Finally an interrogator invited me to sign a document stating that I would discontinue preaching.

01:37:23.930 --> 01:37:27.930
I have given this matter much thought, I said.

01:37:27.930 --> 01:37:38.369
And I would rather live in prison with my relationship with God intact than to be free and lose his approval.

01:37:38.369 --> 01:37:43.369
At that interrogators shouted, You fool.

01:37:43.369 --> 01:37:48.369
All of you will be arrested and sent to Siberia.

01:37:48.369 --> 01:37:53.369
But she was unexpectedly set free at midnight.

01:37:53.369 --> 01:37:57.369
However, was arrested again some time later.

01:37:57.369 --> 01:38:05.369
In the following dramatization, note how a brother shows faith like that of sister's issue and tomb.

01:38:05.369 --> 01:38:24.010
As the world went from bad to worse, I dug deeper into God's word.

01:38:24.010 --> 01:38:44.939
I wanted to stay strong like so many brothers and sisters in the past.

01:38:44.939 --> 01:38:53.380
Those who remain faithful had no special abilities and were inconspicuous.

01:38:53.380 --> 01:39:00.380
Surely all of us must always trust in Jehovah with all our heart.

01:39:00.380 --> 01:39:05.529
I memorized scriptures.

01:39:05.529 --> 01:39:38.930
I knew these words would build my faith and give me the strength I needed to face what was to come.

01:39:38.930 --> 01:39:45.930
To code this week, as local authorities enforce new restrictions on Jehovah's Witnesses, this is coming just 14 days after this.

01:39:45.930 --> 01:40:12.229
Trust in Jehovah and do what is good.

01:40:12.229 --> 01:40:16.229
Reside in the earth and act with faithfulness.

01:40:16.229 --> 01:40:22.229
Find exquisite delight in Jehovah and you will grant you the desires of your heart.

01:40:22.229 --> 01:40:30.340
We had to be more discreet, but we never stopped talking about God's word.

01:40:30.340 --> 01:40:44.399
We had to face many difficulties, but with God's word embedded in our hearts, we faithfully endured to the end.

01:40:44.399 --> 01:40:55.649
How can you imitate the examples discussed in this symposium?

01:40:55.649 --> 01:40:58.649
How can you imitate Sarah?

01:40:58.649 --> 01:41:06.649
Build faith by meditating on Jehovah's goodness to his people and to you personally.

01:41:06.649 --> 01:41:09.649
How can you imitate Rahab?

01:41:09.649 --> 01:41:16.649
Take a firm stand for true worship, even if you have only a limited knowledge of the truth.

01:41:16.649 --> 01:41:21.500
How to imitate Hannah?

01:41:21.500 --> 01:41:29.039
Build faith by taking note of Jehovah's answers to your prayers.

01:41:29.039 --> 01:41:34.039
How can you imitate the captive Israelite girl?

01:41:34.039 --> 01:41:44.039
Young ones show faith by sharing the good news with schoolmates, teachers, and unbelieving family members.

01:41:44.039 --> 01:41:48.039
You can also imitate the mother of Jesus, Mary.

01:41:48.039 --> 01:41:49.039
How?

01:41:49.039 --> 01:41:54.039
Strengthen your faith and trust in Jehovah.

01:41:54.039 --> 01:42:00.930
Carefully examine the scriptures and meditate on them.

01:42:00.930 --> 01:42:03.930
How can you imitate the Phoenician woman?

01:42:03.930 --> 01:42:12.210
Recognize whom Jehovah is using to do his will and associate yourself with them?

01:42:12.210 --> 01:42:17.210
How can you imitate Mary, the sister of Lazarus?

01:42:17.210 --> 01:42:24.210
Build faith by considering all that God's word says about His wonderful promises.

01:42:24.210 --> 01:42:32.210
The Bible says, Mary, set down at the feet of the Lord and kept listening to what He was saying.

01:42:32.210 --> 01:42:39.260
How can you imitate sister's ishi and the tomb?

01:42:39.260 --> 01:42:46.260
Let the power of God's word motivate you to endure faithfully.

01:42:46.260 --> 01:42:52.260
When we clearly perceive the great cloud of witnesses surrounding us,

01:42:52.260 --> 01:42:58.260
we can run with endurance the race that is set before us as Hebrews 12.

01:42:58.260 --> 01:43:02.260
Verse 1 encourages us to do.

01:43:02.260 --> 01:43:08.260
Like these faithful women, we can all be included in Jehovah's book of remembrance,

01:43:08.260 --> 01:43:16.260
as mentioned at Malachi 3.16 and inherit everlasting blessings.

01:43:16.260 --> 01:43:21.819
Thank you, brothers, for those motivating talks.

01:43:21.819 --> 01:43:29.069
